The paper proposes a novel framework for text classification using 3-dimensional tensors and convolutional neural networks. This approach combines techniques from computer vision (3D tensors and convolutional kernels) and natural language processing (text classification). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques for text classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with analyzing and processing text data, which could also make it relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
